# Formatters - Code Formatting

## Built-in Formatters

OpenCode includes built-in support for many formatters:

| Formatter | Languages |
|-----------|-----------|
| air | Go (Air live reload) |
| biome | JavaScript, TypeScript, CSS, JSON |
| cargofmt | Rust |
| clang-format | C, C++, Objective-C |
| dart | Dart |
| gofmt | Go |
| prettier | JavaScript, TypeScript, CSS, HTML, Markdown |
| ruff | Python |
| And many more... | |

## How It Works

When OpenCode generates code changes, it automatically runs the appropriate formatter on the modified files to ensure consistent formatting.

## Configure

Formatters are configured in the `formatters` section of `opencode.json`:

### Disable All
```json
{
  "formatters": {
    "disable": true
  }
}
```

### Disable Specific
```json
{
  "formatters": {
    "disabled": ["prettier", "ruff"]
  }
}
```

## Custom Formatters

Create custom formatters with:

- **command** - The formatter command to run
- **environment** - Environment variables for the formatter
- **extensions** - File extensions the formatter applies to

Use `$FILE` placeholder in the command to reference the file being formatted:
```json
{
  "formatters": {
    "custom": {
      "my-formatter": {
        "command": "my-formatter $FILE",
        "extensions": [".myext"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```
